quran[70]{c,v,t}:
  26,111,"They said, \"How can we believe you when you are followed mostly by the lowest [class of People]"
  26,112,"He said, \"What do I know about what they have been doing"
  26,113,"It is for my Lord alone to bring them to account, if you [could] only understand"
  26,114,I am not one to drive away the believers
  26,115,I am only a clear warner
  26,116,"They said, \"If you do not desist, Noah, you will surely be stoned"
  26,117,"He said, \"My Lord, my people have denied me"
  26,118,"Judge between us decisively, and save me and those believers with me"
  26,119,So We saved him and those with him in the laden ark
  26,120,and then We drowned the rest
  26,121,"There is a sign in this, but most of them will not believe"
  26,122,"Truly your Lord is the Almighty, the Merciful-to-all"
  26,123,"[The people of] Aad denied the Messengers"
  26,124,"when their brother Hud said to them, \"Will you not be mindful of God"
  26,125,I am a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,126,"so be mindful of God, and obey me"
  26,127,I ask no reward from you for doing this; my reward is only from the Lord of the worlds
  26,128,Do you build a tower on every hill just to amuse yourselves
  26,129,and construct for yourselves mighty castles hoping to live there eternally
  26,130,"And when you attack, why do you attack like tyrants"
  26,131,"So be mindful of God, and obey me"
  26,132,and be mindful of Him Who provided you with everything you know
  26,133,grazing livestock and children
  26,134,gardens and springs
  26,135,I fear for you the punishment of a terrible day
  26,136,"They said, \"It is all the same to us whether you preach or not"
  26,137,this is only what our forefathers used to do
  26,138,We will not be punished
  26,139,"They denied him, so We destroyed them. There is a sign in this, but most of them will not believe"
  26,140,"Truly your Lord is the Almighty, the Merciful-to-all"
  26,141,"[The people of] Thamud denied the Messengers"
  26,142,"when their brother Salih said to them, \"Will you not be mindful of God"
  26,143,I am a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,144,"so be mindful of God, and obey me"
  26,145,"I ask no reward from you for doing this; my reward [comes) only from the Lord of the worlds"
  26,146,Do you think that you will be left secure in what you have here
  26,147,"[your] gardens and springs"
  26,148,fields of crops and palm trees with softened fruit
  26,149,And your fine homes that you skillfully carve out of the mountains
  26,150,Be mindful of God and obey me
  26,151,and do not obey those given to excess
  26,152,who spread corruption on earth and do not set things right
  26,153,"They said, \"You are bewitched"
  26,154,"You are only a man like us, so bring a sign, if you are telling the truth"
  26,155,"He said, \"This is a camel. She will have a time to drink, and you will have a time, [each) on an appointed day"
  26,156,"Do not harm her, unless you want to be seized by the punishment of a terrible day"
  26,157,But they hamstrung her and woke up fully regretful
  26,158,"and the punishment seized them. There is a sign in this, but most of them will not believe"
  26,159,"Truly your Lord is the Almighty, the Merciful-to-all"
  26,160,The People of Lot denied the Messengers
  26,161,"When their brother Lot said to them, \"Will you not be mindful of God"
  26,162,I am a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,163,"So be mindful of God, and obey me"
  26,164,I ask no reward from you for doing this; my reward comes only from the Lord of the worlds
  26,165,Why do you get intimate with men
  26,166,and leave the mates your Lord has created for you? You people have transgressed all bounds
  26,167,"They said, \"If you do not stop this, Lot, you will surely be kicked out"
  26,168,"He said, \"I despise your actions"
  26,169,"My Lord, save me and my family from (the consequence of] what they do"
  26,170,"So We saved him and his family, all of them"
  26,171,except for an old woman who stayed behind
  26,172,"Then, We destroyed the others"
  26,173,We poured upon them a rain of destruction. How terrible is such rain on those who had been forewarned
  26,174,"There is a sign in this, but most of them will not believe"
  26,175,"Truly, your Lord is the Almighty, the Merciful-to-all"
  26,176,The woods-dwellers denied the Messengers
  26,177,"When Shu'ayb said to them, \"Will you not be mindful of God"
  26,178,I am a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,179,"so be mindful of God, and obey me"
  26,180,I ask no reward from you for doing this; my reward comes only from the Lord of the worlds